  "text": "## Dashboard JSON Schema Version Migration Pipeline\n\nThe Grafana dashboard migration system is a comprehensive two-layer pipeline with backend (Go) and frontend (TypeScript) implementations that work in tandem to evolve dashboard schemas across versions.\n\n### Backend Migration Pipeline (Go)\n\n**Entry Point - Migration Runner**\n- `apps/dashboard/pkg/migration/migrate.go`: The main migration orchestrator\n  - `Migrate()` function: Public API that migrates a dashboard to a target version\n  - `Initialize()` function: Sets up the migrator singleton with dependencies (DataSourceInfoProvider)\n  - Internal `migrator` struct: Manages the migration state and execution with singleton pattern\n  - Execution flow: Applies frontend defaults, tracks transformations, runs version-to-version migrations, adds built-in annotations, cleans up for save\n\n**Migration Registry**\n- `apps/dashboard/pkg/migration/schemaversion/migrations.go`: Central registry of all migrations\n  - `GetMigrations(dsInfoProvider)` function: Returns a map[int]SchemaVersionMigrationFunc of all available migration functions (versions 2-42)\n  - `GetSchemaVersion()` function: Extracts the current schema version from a dashboard\n  - Defines `SchemaVersionMigrationFunc` type signature: func(context.Context, map[string]interface{}) error\n  - LATEST_VERSION constant = 42 (final version for v1 dashboard API)\n  - MIN_VERSION constant = 0 (minimum supported version for migration)\n\n**Individual Migration Steps (42 versions total)**\nEach version file implements a specific schema evolution:\n\n- **V2** (apps/dashboard/pkg/migration/schemaversion/v2.go): Migrates legacy services.filter structure to time and templating.list\n- **V3-V15**: Various panel and dashboard structure refinements\n- **V16**: Grid layout migration (from row-based to grid-based positioning)\n- **V17-V32**: Progressive improvements to panel options, data links, transformations, and value mappings\n- **V33** (apps/dashboard/pkg/migration/schemaversion/v33.go): Datasource name to reference migration (string names → objects with uid/type)\n- **V34**: CloudWatch query migrations for multiple statistics\n- **V35**: X-axis visibility fixes for time series panels\n- **V36** (apps/dashboard/pkg/migration/schemaversion/v36.go): Critical datasource reference stabilization - converts null datasources to proper defaults, handles annotation and variable datasources, manages panel and target-level datasource consistency\n- **V37-V42**: Recent refinements to legend configuration, table cell options, time series table transformations, refresh types, deprecated properties, and hideFrom functionality\n\n**Supporting Utilities**\n- `apps/dashboard/pkg/migration/schemaversion/migration_utils.go`: Shared utility functions for common migration patterns\n- `apps/dashboard/pkg/migration/schemaversion/datasource_utils.go`: Datasource reference handling and conversion utilities\n- `apps/dashboard/pkg/migration/schemaversion/errors.go`: Custom error types for migration failures\n\n### Frontend Migration Pipeline (TypeScript)\n\n**Main Implementation**\n- `public/app/features/dashboard/state/DashboardMigrator.ts`: The frontend DashboardMigrator class\n  - `DashboardMigrator` class: Wraps a DashboardModel and provides updateSchema() method\n  - `updateSchema(old, targetSchemaVersion)` method: Implements version-to-version migrations in TypeScript\n  - `DASHBOARD_SCHEMA_VERSION` constant = 42 (matches backend final version)\n  - Mirrors backend logic while handling frontend-specific concerns (DashboardModel and PanelModel constructors, panel plugin migrations, etc.)\n\n**Key Frontend Migration Patterns**\nThe TypeScript implementation handles:\n- Legacy services.filter migration (v2)\n- Panel type auto-migrations (table → table-old, singlestat → stat)\n- Annotation and variable datasource migrations\n- CloudWatch query standardization\n- Field configuration and value mapping transformations\n- Panel upgrade handlers that apply transformations after each schema version\n- Special row panel handling for grid layout (v16)\n\n### Migration Execution Architecture\n\n**Backend Flow**\n1. Initialize(): Set up migrations map via GetMigrations()\n2. Migrate(): For each version from current to target, execute the registered SchemaVersionMigrationFunc\n3. Each V* function receives context and dashboard map, modifies in-place, returns error\n4. Frontend defaults applied before migrations, cleanup applied after\n\n**Frontend Flow**\n1. DashboardMigrator constructor: Takes DashboardModel instance\n2. updateSchema(): Executes version-specific transformations as panelUpgrades\n3. Panel upgrades collected and applied to all panels (including nested in rows)\n4. Schema version updated after all migrations complete\n\n**Synchronization**\n- Both implementations target the same DASHBOARD_SCHEMA_VERSION (42)\n- Backend V33 (datasource name→ref) mirrors frontend v33 migration\n- Backend V36 (datasource reference stabilization) mirrors frontend v36 migration\n- Migration order and logic are intentionally identical to ensure frontend/backend consistency\n\n### Key Migration Examples\n\n**V2 Migration**: Legacy services.filter structure consolidation\n- Before: services.filter.time and services.filter.list at old.services\n- After: dashboard.time and dashboard.templating.list\n\n**V36 Migration** (DataSourceInfoProvider-based): Critical for datasource portability\n- Converts string datasource references to structured objects with uid, type, and apiVersion\n- Handles null datasources by setting them to the default datasource\n- Processes annotations, template variables, and all panel targets\n- Maintains consistency between panel-level and target-level datasource references\n- Preserves special datasources like Mixed ('-- Mixed --') and expression ('__expr__')\n- Essential for dashboard export/import across different Grafana instances\n\n### Design Patterns\n\n1. **Version-to-Function Mapping**: GetMigrations() returns a map allowing direct lookup and incremental execution\n2. **Stateful Migrator**: Singleton pattern ensures consistent migration state\n3. **In-Place Modification**: Dashboards modified as map[string]interface{} for flexibility\n4. **Provider Injection**: DataSourceInfoProvider injected for context-aware migrations (V33, V36)\n5. **Frontend Defaults First**: Backend applies frontend constructor defaults before migrations\n6. **Panel Upgrade Handlers**: Frontend uses array of upgrade functions applied uniformly\n\n### Scope and Limitations\n\n- **Final Schema**: Version 42 is the final version for the v1 dashboard API (noted in code comments)\n- **No Future Migrations**: Explicit warnings prevent adding new schema migrations\n- **Panel-Specific Migrations**: Future improvements should use panel plugin migration handlers instead\n- **Frontend/Backend Parity**: Both implementations must remain synchronized for consistency"
}

